ce:section.ce:para:
In order to elucidate the interaction between GQDs and LA, the thermodynamic parameters were calculated using ITC studies. The calorimetric experiment was carried out at room temperature (298 ± 1 K). A total of 19 serial injections, each containing 2 μL of serum-LA mixture was transferred into the cell containing 180 μL of GQDs. The syringe was stirred at a speed of 750 rpm and a gap of 120 s was maintained between two successive injections. The corresponding data were fitted using one set of sites model (Fig. 9
                           ). A negative value of change in Gibbs free energy (ΔG) indicates spontaneity of the interaction between GQDs and lactic acid (ΔG = −5.72 kcal mol−1). The changes of enthalpy (ΔH) can be considered as an indication of increase of intermolecular bond energies in binding process. ΔH was found to be highly negative with a value of −80.0 kcal mol−1, which suggests exothermic bonding interactions between GQDs and lactic acid. Such high negative value of ΔH suggests that the interaction between GQDs and LA is an “enthalpy driven” process. The change in entropy (ΔS) was found to have a small negative value −0.25 kcal mol−1 K−1. Although there is small negative change in entropy, the process is thermodynamically favorable. The small negative ΔS could be owing to the condition of the medium that prevailed in serum that contains a large number of biomolecules and renders a restricted environment. The binding dissociation constant (Kd) value for the interaction between GQDs and lactic acid was found to be very low 64.0 × 10−6 M indicating greater binding affinity between the two interacting molecules (Table 7
                           ).
